args: The front line won't hold much longer,\nJoachim! What's our move here?!
Right, let's see...\nWe give that position up for now and\nshore up defenses at point C.
Point F is prepped and ready, Joachim.\nAwaiting orders!
...Rrgh. These guys are really going all-in.\nThey've got zero intention of giving ground!
We HAVE to have put a dent in them by\nthis point. Just how much are they paying\nthese guys, anyway?
Guess it just proves how big a threat\nthey think Commander Kirsty is.
They're not wrong—she's a beast. But I\ndon't see this stalemate lasting for long.
They'll make their move before much—
...Enemy shows signs of preparing a\nfinal, all-out assault?
The crazy fools have gone suicidal...\nWhat kind of scale are we talking here?
D-definitely enough to breach the front\nbarricade. It...it won't last long!
Ugh, fantastic. There's fearless, and then\nthere's...whatever this is.
(They're a lot more dangerous than the\nnumbers suggest if they're willing to die.\nWe'll need to take risks to match that.)
(If we want to keep casualties down,\nwe have to intercept them early and stop\nthe push before things spiral out of hand.)
(But there's no way we get through that in\none piece... Can I really own a decision I\nknow is gonna result in losses?)
What do you think, Joachim?\nAny brilliant ideas?
Sorry, fresh out. This is a tricky one.
If even YOU say so, it must be true. Guess\nthat means we'll just have to tough it out.
In that case, I think we should scale back\ndefenses elsewhere and protect the center\nwith our lives. Sound okay, Joachim?
R-right. Though we'll never hold if they\nbreak through from anywhere else. Let's\nleave a flying column at the midpoint.
Noelle, relay those orders to the others!
(But why can't I shake this feeling?\nThis...dread?)
One hour later, at the front gates of Kirsty's base...
Dammit! Fall back for now! We'll regroup,\nthen crush them for good!
S-sorry, Aggie... I think this is...\nas far as I go...

Marsh! Ugh, dammit! We've got multiple
wounded! Everybody who can still move,
get these people inside! Medics, we need
you now!
We're not out of this thing yet; we need to\nhurry up, before they come at us again.
Damn, I didn't think they'd be this tough.\nSpeaking of, how's Marsh doing?
He's, um, in critical condition. Medical is\ndoing everything they can for him, but...
I won't let his sacrifice be in vain.\nWe need a plan before the next wave...\nBut, er, but what options do we have?
Joachim, what do you think? Joachim?
If I gave better orders—if I was prepared\nto do whatever it took and own up—then\nthis wouldn't have happened.
It's my fault they got Marsh...\nIt's my fault my sister is gone.
Joachim? The hell you talking about?
If I had only known the weight of that\nresponsibility back then... The weight\nof holding a person's life in your hands...
I'm sorry, everyone, but I need to...um...\ntalk to Joachim about a...thing!
Gonna borrow him for a second okay bye!
We need a minute to regroup here,\nanyway, so you can have your second.
...Huh. I don't think I've ever heard Noelle\nraise her voice before.
And what was WITH Joachim, anyway?
